author: KIRO 7 STAFF
title: Kent police investigate fatal shooting in Target parking lot
text:
Shoppers in Kent will be able to get their cars that were blocked by a murder scene in a Target store parking lot.
The fatal shooting happened in a strip mall parking lot at 104 th Avenue Southeast at 7 p.m.Wednesday night.
Police investigating a homicide in the Kent target parking lot, you can see a shot of SUV in one of the pictures pic.twitter.com/lRIPnJTQgV
— Henry Rosoff (@HenryKIRO7) October 1, 2015 Officials released surveillance images of a suspect vehicle involved in the shooting. Police said a late 80s or early 90s white or silver Toyota Corolla pulled up alongside an SUV.
Target security caught the suspect vehicle, white or gray Corolla please RT pic.twitter.com/V0ChhhQAyz
— Henry Rosoff (@HenryKIRO7) October 1, 2015 According to police, there was some sort of confrontation and a man in the Corolla opened fire on the SUV. The 23-year-old Kent man inside the SUV was killed and the vehicle rolled into several others. A dog inside the SUV was unharmed.
Some shoppers stranded by this investigation near Target because their vehicles are in the crime scene area pic.twitter.com/yjyTIFlzNY
— Henry Rosoff (@HenryKIRO7) October 1, 2015 According to witnesses, there appeared to be two suspects inside the fleeing Corolla. There is no description of the suspects.
A shopper who was inside the store when the gunfire erupted explained what he happened.
"I was at the checkout stand and I heard one guy say,' I'm not going out there.' He said, 'I'm not getting carts, there's bullets flying,' and I came out here and went 'Oh, no.'"
While police investigated, two dozen cars belonging to shoppers remained trapped inside an active crime scene. As of 11:30 p.m. Wednesday, many were still waiting to get their cars.
Police do not have any additional information about the two men in the Corolla, nor do they know why the men were meeting, but the shooting is not believed to be random.
Anyone with information on the shooting is urged to call police.
The Target store appears that it will be open Thursday.
